title.narrative: STRENGTHENING SUPPLY

description.narrative: Capacity of health facilities in selected marginalized districts strengthened to provide a complete and integrated package for equitable maternal, new born, and child health services (Essential Health Package) by 2018, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Health And Emergencies, Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 80% of pregnant women and children under five utilize quality high impact maternal, neonatal and young child survival services by 2018.
